      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented with fluid temperature ±1 °C, haematocrit ±2%, flow rate ±0.1 L/min, rotational speed ±10 RPM; boundary conditions in CFD match experimental set-points within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA-protocol in-vitro hemolysis tests were conducted at 37 °C ± 0.5 °C with bovine blood at 33% haematocrit ± 1.5%. Flow and speed set-points were logged at 1 Hz; time-averaged values used as CFD boundary conditions. All tolerances satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH within ±15% of experimentally measured RH at each of the 5 operating points; systematic bias < 5%.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RH values at all 5 operating points fall within ±12% of experimental measurements. Mean signed error is +3.1% (slight over-prediction). The 6 L/min / 3500 RPM point shows the largest deviation at +11.4%, within the ±15% criterion. Output comparison is satisfactory at level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the regulatory decision criterion; mapping from CFD scalar output to RH is documented and traceable.",
      "rationale": "RH is computed as the ratio of normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) of the test pump to that of the predicate device under identical conditions, consistent with FDA guidance on hemolysis testing. The mapping from CFD-integrated hemolysis power-law scalar to NIH is fully documented in the simulation protocol."
    },
    {
